President Obama has issued a proclamation declaring December 15, 2015, as Bill of Rights Day. This day commemorates the ratification of the Bill of Rights in 1791, which was a significant step towards ensuring the ideals of equality, liberty, and justice for all Americans. The proclamation acknowledges the ongoing work of each generation in upholding these principles and calls upon the people of the United States to observe this day with appropriate ceremonies and activities. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of the Bill of Rights in protecting fundamental liberties and enabling citizens to bring about positive change in their democracy.